title: Albert, Grimes questionable for Dolphins’ game at Tennessee
text:
Home » News » Sports » NFL » Albert, Grimes questionable for… Albert, Grimes questionable for Dolphins’ game at Tennessee By The Associated Press October 16, 2015 2:31 pm 
DAVIE, Fla. (AP) — Left tackle Branden Albert is questionable for the Miami Dolphins’ game Sunday at Tennessee because of a left hamstring injury that forced him to miss the past two games. 
Cornerback Brent Grimes is also questionable with a knee injury. Both were limited in practice for a third day in a row Friday. 
Tight end Dion Sims is probable to return from a concussion that has sidelined him since the season opener.
